config SOC_THEJAS32
	select RISCV
	select INCLUDE_RESET_VECTOR
	select RISCV_SOC_INTERRUPT_INIT
	select ATOMIC_OPERATIONS_C
	help
	  Enable support for the C-DAC THEJAS32 SoC.

	  THEJAS32 is built around the VEGA ET1031, a 32-bit (RV32IM) single-core,
	  in-order, 3-stage pipeline RISC-V processor designed by C-DAC as part of
	  India's Digital India RISC-V (DIR-V) programme. The image is loaded into
	  and executed from internal SRAM, so execute-in-place (XIP) is not used.

	  The SoC follows the RISC-V privileged specification for trap handling but
	  uses a custom (non-PLIC) interrupt controller, so it provides its own
	  interrupt management instead of selecting RISCV_PRIVILEGED.
